    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This technique can only be used while the user currently resides within the shadow of a willing ally. When an opponent attacks the user's 'host' with an attack or technique that puts him in melee range, the user can manipulate his host's shadow, bending it into contact with his opponent's shadow and using it as a transfer gateway to become a part of his opponent's shadow. The user may then initiate a special grapple from behind with a garrote wire in his possession. This special grapple gives him a +4 to his initial attack and a +4 to maintain the grapple as he attempts to petrify his opponent through shadow arts while physically strangling him. If the user succeeds the grapple check, his allies gain a +8 bonus to successfully hit the right opponent as per grappling rules.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Shadow Arts (f), Dead Space Concealment (t)</p>\n<p><b>Material Focus:</b> Garrote Wire.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
